reviews.text: Northern Rail decided to introduce a daily charge for this small, un-attended carpark in October 2017. This is yet more evidence that Northern Rail are ignoring genuine demand from rural communities and I've been driving to work since the charges came into effect. Thanks for looking after your hundreds of genuine commuters Northern Rail.
Good service to leeds and Huddersfield got everything it needs for the how many people use it
No facilities and don't expect your bike to be in one piece or there when you return if you cycle. Also parking charges are now in place. No CCTV and platform lights work intermittently.

Parking poor and now charged for. Hardly any shelter and poor access to leeds/Huddersfield  bound platform especially for disabled. Only 3 disabled parking spaces .... Leeds platform access 1/4 mile away down a hill under a bridge on a main road and then up a long stepped incline. Not good enough. Would give 0 star if possible
